parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trailer brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when towing heavy trailers.
symptoms: The brake pedal rapidly goes to the floor
the vehicle freewheels through a stop
the brake pedal overheats
the brake pedal does not respond properly
the vehicle is unable to slow down or stop as expected
warning lights may illuminate with a "service trailer brakes" message.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose power, resulting in a loss of power steering and power brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
shuts down
or dies while driving
especially when driving uphill; loss of power steering and power brakes; warning indicators illuminate on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS and brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking functionality, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS
Service Trailer Brake
Service Power Steering
and Service Stabilitrak warning indicators illuminate; loss of braking functionality; failure occurs while towing a trailer or not towing a trailer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel speed sensor can cause the vehicle to lose braking functionality and stability, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS
Service Trailer Brake
Service Power Steering
and Service Stabilitrak warning indicators illuminate; loss of braking functionality; failure occurs while towing a trailer or not towing a trailer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vibration of the steering system can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes or vibrates while driving at high speeds (70-78 mph) on the highway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The flickering or shaking of the HID headlights can cause distraction to the driver and other road users, potentially leading to accidents, especially when driving on rough road surfaces.
symptoms: The HID headlights flicker or shake like blinking eyes
dim and brighten
or exhibit an on/off pattern while driving on bumpy surfaces.
